text: Raghuji I (Raghuji Bhonsle); 1695 - 14 February 1755) was a Maratha general of the Bhonsle clan who established the Nagpur Kingdom in much of east-central India during the reign of Chhatrapati Shahu I. His successors ruled the kingdom until 1853. == References == Category:Pages created with the Article Wizard from 2024 Category:1695 births Category:1755 deaths Category:18th century in India
